.TH NEXUS-QUERY 1 "November 2025" "Nexus CLI 0.11.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nexus-query \- execute Cypher queries against Nexus database
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nexus query
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIQUERY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Execute Cypher queries against the Nexus graph database.
Supports direct query execution, file-based queries, and interactive REPL mode.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Execute queries from a file. Use "-" to read from stdin.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Start interactive REPL mode.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-params " " \fIJSON\fR
Query parameters as JSON object.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Execute a simple query:
.B nexus query "MATCH (n) RETURN n LIMIT 5"
.TP
Query with parameters:
.B nexus query "MATCH (n) WHERE n.name = $name RETURN n" --params '{"name": "Alice"}'
.TP
Execute from file:
.B nexus query --file queries.cypher
.TP
Interactive mode:
.B nexus query --interactive
.TP
JSON output:
.B nexus --json query "MATCH (n) RETURN n"
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
In interactive mode, you can:
.IP \(bu 2
Enter multi-line queries (end with semicolon)
.IP \(bu 2
Use up/down arrows for history
.IP \(bu 2
Type 'exit' or 'quit' to exit
.IP \(bu 2
Press Ctrl+C to cancel current input
.IP \(bu 2
Press Ctrl+D to exit
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nexus (1)
